Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Motion hearing on January 9, 2023 at 11:00 am.
Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.

3:00 PM Court calls case. Da Kelz states appearances. Defendant Zachary D. Sunn appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer in court for Zachary D. Sunn.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states all Victim's Rights Legislations have been complied with.  DA Kelz calls witness: Dominick Koller an Officer with the Park Falls Police Department. Witness sworn. Direct questioning by DA Kelz. Witness identifies the defendant on record. Witness excused. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Bond is to continue.

1:17 PM Defendant Zachary D. Sunn appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer appeared by video for Zachary D. Sunn.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. Court states there are signature bonds in cases 22CF79 and 22CF80 and that there is a cash bond in case 22CF82. Attorney Restemayer states the Motion was filed to address the cash bond. Court makes comments., Attorney Restemayer addresses his Motion and gives statements in support of the Motion. DA Kelz gives statements in opposition of Attorney Restemayer's Motion. Court addresses the parties in regards to statements made by parties and the courts position on the Motion. Court states it will not make a ruling on the motion today, gives options for modifying the bond to allow treatment to occur. Court orders the bond to remain as is at this time.

Defendant may not have contact with the individual(s): C.M.B. Unless a written waiver is filed with the Clerk of Courts Office OR The Price County Sheriff's Office outside of normal business hours.
**No Contact includes: Going to or remaining in any place the individual resides, is employed at, attends school at, or any public location the individual is temporarily located. Contact through means of telephone. Electronic devices, Social media, email, regular mail, or a 3rd party individual is prohibited. The only exception to this order is contact through your attorney or law enforcement in appropriate circumstances.
